Platform Buddy v159
Plate time-series tracking and multi-rep VBT analysis

Summary
- Changed the standard VBT workflow from two-point measurement to plate time-series tracking.
- The user selects the plate at the lift-specific start position.
- The tracked vertical path is smoothed and split into reps by lift movement pattern.
- Each rep now reports eccentric and concentric velocity metrics.
- The last-rep concentric mean velocity is used by the personal RPE velocity profile.
- Manual two-point measurement remains only as a fallback.

Changed functions in video.js
- getVbtStartGuide(lift)
  Returns SQ/BP/DL-specific start-position instructions and movement patterns.
- trackPlateTimeSeries(dialog, record)
  Runs the standard plate time-series analysis workflow.
- smoothTrackPath(path)
  Applies median and moving-average smoothing to the tracked path.
- pathTurningPoints(path)
  Finds vertical direction changes used for rep segmentation.
- detectRepPhases(path, lift, expectedReps)
  Splits SQ/BP top-bottom-top and DL bottom-top-bottom movements into reps.
- phaseVelocityMetric(path, phase, metersPerPixel)
  Calculates mean/peak velocity, duration, and distance for one phase.
- calculateRepVelocityMetrics(repPhases, calibration)
  Produces eccentric/concentric metrics, ROM, confidence, and warnings per rep.
- getPrimaryVbtMetric(metrics)
  Produces last/best/first concentric velocity, velocity loss, and detected reps.
- validateRepDetection(metrics, expectedReps)
  Warns when rep detection is unstable or does not match expected reps.
- renderRepVelocityTable(metrics)
  Renders the multi-rep velocity table.
- trackPlateRoiPath(dialog, record)
  Increased time-series sampling and connected rep detection and metrics.
- autoTrackingConfidence(...)
  Adjusted path-travel confidence thresholds for multi-rep round trips.
- adaptVbtRecord(record)
  Preserves legacy records and uses final-rep concentric velocity for RPE profiles.
- vbtResultMarkup(data)
  Displays set average, last/best rep, velocity loss, and per-rep results.
- vbtCardMarkup(record)
  Shows lift-specific start-position guidance and the new standard workflow.
- saveVbtVelocity(button, mode)
  Saves primary VBT metrics and multi-rep measurement data.

Data compatibility
- Existing video and VBT records remain supported.
- New records use measurement.mode = "plate-roi-timeseries".
- Existing averageVelocity stores set-average concentric velocity.
- lastRepVelocity and primaryVbtMetric.lastRepConcentricMeanVelocity store the profile metric.
- platform-pr-v3 and app.js were not changed.

Validation
- video.js, app.js, and sw.js syntax checks passed.
- Synthetic path test detected SQ 5/5 reps and DL 3/3 reps.
- Synthetic tests produced per-rep eccentric/concentric metrics and primary VBT metrics.
- index.html details/section tag counts match.
- manifest.webmanifest JSON parse passed.
- PWA cache/query/start_url are aligned to v159.
- app.js SHA256 matches v157.

Known limitations
- Tracking quality still depends on camera stability, lighting, plate visibility, and a correct ROI.
- Real-video accuracy must be verified after device upload with SQ/BP/DL sample videos.
- Manual top/bottom marker correction is not implemented yet.
- Pause detection is stored as optional and is not yet reliable enough for coaching decisions.
- Velocity curve graphs and overlay-video export remain future work.
- This remains post-set video analysis, not real-time VBT hardware.
